⁸ Leqatus] The Legati were next the general in power, and used to command, by his appointment, some part of the army in the day of battle, and the whole in the general’s absence. There were several of them in an army, and the general commonly used them as his coun- sellors or advisers in all cases of importance or difficulty—M.
